The National Directorate of Employment (NDE) has distributed tools and cash as resettlement loans to 11 Kaduna graduates out of the 416 Environmental Beatification Training Scheme (EBTS) trained nationwide. The selected beneficiaries were selected out of the 1850 trained youths graduates under the 2018 EBTS of the NDE to be able to unlock their potentials as leaders to take the country into the future as well as maximise the qualities of their lives. Speaking at the disbursement ceremony Kaduna NDE Director-General Nasiru Mohammed Ladan Argungu whose speech was read by the State NDE Coordinator ‎Sani Mohammed Maiwada said the NDE has been strongly supportive and has consistently invested in Nigerian Youths. He explained that” NDE has provided requisite tools and cash to a total of 416 graduates of EBTS in the 36 states including FCT ‎to start and grow their businesses as budding landscaping service operators. 11 graduates out of the number were Kaduna citizens. The training will  boost job creation and make the youths to contribute their quota to the national economy, “ he said.  NDE distributes resettlement loan to 416 EBTS Trainees NDE distributes tools, cash to youths in Taraba NDE disburses resettlement loan to 11 graduates in Imo Kindly take one minute (1) of your time to fill out this short question. This questionnaire is designed to sample readers' opinions regarding what the feel about Daily Trust newspaper advertisement; it is not intended to used for any purpose other than to improve the quality of our newspapers. Any information provided will therefore be treated as confidential.